# CelebConnect — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
CelebConnect is a cross-platform React Native (Expo) mobile app that:
- Lets users add birthday/anniversary events to a calendar
- Automatically sends WhatsApp messages and Instagram posts on event days
- Supports iOS and Android

## Tech Stack
- React Native + Expo SDK 52
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- React Navigation v6 (Stack + Bottom Tabs)
- Zustand (state management)
- AsyncStorage (local persistence)
- expo-secure-store (auth tokens)
- react-native-calendars (calendar UI)
- react-native-paper (UI components)

## Code Style
- Use functional components with hooks only (no class components)
- All files must be TypeScript (.tsx / .ts)
- Import aliases: @screens, @components, @context, @hooks, @utils, @services, @types
- Use StyleSheet.create() for all styles
- Colors and spacing from src/utils/theme.ts
- Prefer named exports for components, default exports for screens

## File Structure
src/
  screens/      # auth/, home/, calendar/, account/
  components/   # common/, calendar/, auth/
  navigation/   # AppNavigator.tsx
  context/      # AuthContext.tsx, EventContext.tsx
  hooks/        # custom hooks
  utils/        # theme.ts, helpers.ts
  types/        # index.ts
  services/     # API calls (WhatsApp, Instagram)

## Key Features to Implement
1. Auth: Login (email/phone), Register, Forgot Password
2. Home: Upcoming events dashboard
3. Calendar: Add/edit/delete events with recurrence
4. Auto-messaging: WhatsApp Business API + Instagram Graph API
5. Account: Profile editing, notification settings

## When generating code:
- Always add TypeScript types
- Include error handling with try/catch
- Use COLORS from theme for all color values
- Follow existing component patterns in the codebase
